Filtering for our countries

Our fellows today come from: Croatia - Dr. Kristian Dosen, investigative reporter and a professor at University of Zagreb Czech Republic - Filip Rozanek, editor of Digizonecz India - Joseph Kootungal Jose, radio host for Entertainment Network Limited Pakistan - Naeem Akbar Sahoutara, reporter, Dawn Palestine - Haneen Baker, Head of English Department, An-Najah National University Nigeria - Aniekeme Finbarr Uklong, special assistant to the governor, Akwa Ibom State Vietnam - Tien Ahn Tuan Nguyen, head of visual desk, Dan Tri newspaper Lithuania - Martynas Vainutis, editor, UAB Kasko Group

gapminder_filtered <- gapminder %>% 
  filter(country=="Croatia"|
         country=="Czech Republic"|
         country=="India"|
         country=="Pakistan"|
         country=="Palestine"|
         country=="Nigeria"|
         country=="Vietnam"|
         country=="Lithuania")

visually

ggplot(gapminder_filtered, aes(gdpPercap, lifeExp, size = pop, colour = country)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7, show.legend = TRUE) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = country_colors) +
  scale_size(range = c(2, 12)) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  labs(title = 'Year: {frame_time}', x = 'GDP per capita', y = 'life expectancy') +
  transition_time(year) +
  ease_aes('linear')

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
